README.md
     1‚Üí# peepDB
     3‚Üí**peepDB** is an open-source command-line tool and Python library designed for developers and database administrators who need a fast and efficient way to inspect their database tables without writing SQL queries. With support for MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, SQLite, MongoDB, Firebase, MSSQL and OracleDB. peepDB is lightweight, secure, and incredibly easy to use.
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí## üöÄ Features
     7‚Üí- **Multi-Database Support**: Works with MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, SQLite, MongoDB, MSSQL, OracleDB, and Firebase.
     8‚Üí- **Quick Data Inspection**: View all tables or a specific table with a simple command.
     9‚Üí- **User-Friendly CLI**: Easy-to-use command-line interface powered by Click.
    10‚Üí- **Secure Local Storage**: Securely store database connection details with encryption on your local machine.
    11‚Üí- **Lightweight**: Minimal footprint, designed for speed.
    12‚Üí- **Formatted Output**: View data in a clean, formatted table or JSON format.
    13‚Üí- **Pagination**: Efficiently handle large datasets by viewing data in manageable chunks.
    14‚Üí
    15‚Üí## üé¨ peepDB in Action
    17‚ÜíHere's a quick demonstration of peepDB:
    18‚Üí
    19‚Üí![peepDB Demo](images/demo.gif)
    20‚Üí
    21‚Üí## üñºÔ∏è peepDB stills
    25‚Üí> **Note:** The above image reflects the commands used in the official release (v0.1.3)
    26‚Üí
    27‚Üí## üì¶ Installation
    29‚ÜíYou can install peepDB directly from PyPI:
    30‚Üí
    31‚Üí```bash
    32‚Üípip install peepdb
    33‚Üí```
    34‚Üí
    35‚Üí## üõÝÔ∏è Usage
    37‚ÜípeepDB uses a command-based structure for easier and more intuitive use. Here are the main commands with examples:
