     1‚Üí# just-the-docs-template
     3‚ÜíThis is a *bare-minimum* template to create a [Jekyll] site that:
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí- uses the [Just the Docs] theme;
     6‚Üí- can be built and published on [GitHub Pages];
     7‚Üí- can be built and previewed locally, and published on other platforms.
     8‚Üí
     9‚ÜíMore specifically, the created site:
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí- uses a gem-based approach, i.e. uses a `Gemfile` and loads the `just-the-docs` gem;
    12‚Üí- uses the [GitHub Pages / Actions workflow] to build and publish the site on GitHub Pages.
    13‚Üí
    14‚ÜíTo get started with creating a site, simply:
    15‚Üí
    16‚Üí1. click "[use this template]" to create a GitHub repository
    17‚Üí2. go to Settings > Pages > Build and deployment > Source, and select GitHub Actions
    18‚Üí
    19‚ÜíIf you want to maintain your docs in the `docs` directory of an existing project repo, see [Hosting your docs from an existing project repo](#hosting-your-docs-from-an-existing-project-repo).
    20‚Üí
    21‚ÜíAfter completing the creation of your new site on GitHub, update it as needed:
